<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="437" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d437">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/489: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Damm</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-02T18:00:00-05:00">April 2, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Press despatches of today from Naco report that Mexican rebel airplane
                            this morning bombed Naco, Arizona causing injury to American citizen.
                            Telegraph facts immediately to reach Department not later than nine
                            o’clock Wednesday morning. Similar telegram sent to Agua Prieta.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>